RT  Mycothiol-dependent proteins in actinomycetes.
RA  Rawat M, Av-Gay Y;
RL  FEMS Microbiol Rev. 2007;31:278-292.
CC  Mycothiol is a glutathione analog common in the Actinobacteria, but not
CC  found elsewhere. This Genome Property provides a higher-level view of
CC  mycothiol metabolism that includes its synthesis (GenProp0753), the
CC  regeneration of mycothiol from mycothione (its disulfide-bonded dimer)
CC  by NADPH-dependent reduction, and a guild of mycothiol-dependent
CC  enzymes, the discovery of which is incomplete.
**  Mycothiol-Dependent Maleylpyruvate Isomerase not yet modeled, but has a
**  domain model, kind of.
